You can provide project data in JSON format when making API requests. Below are the details for both saving a project and assigning a project to an employee.


---

1️⃣ Save a Project (POST /projects)

Use this API to create a new project before assigning it to employees.

Request (JSON)

{
    "projectName": "AI Development"
}

cURL Example

curl -X POST "http://localhost:8080/projects" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{
    "projectName": "AI Development"
}'

Response

{
    "id": 1,
    "projectName": "AI Development",
    "employees": []
}


---

2️⃣ Assign Projects to an Employee (PUT /employees/{id}/assign-projects)

Use this API to assign existing projects to an employee. You need to pass an array of project objects with their IDs.

Request (JSON)

[
    {
        "id": 1,
        "projectName": "AI Development"
    },
    {
        "id": 2,
        "projectName": "Cloud Migration"
    }
]

cURL Example

curl -X PUT "http://localhost:8080/employees/1/assign-projects" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '[
    {
        "id": 1,
        "projectName": "AI Development"
    },
    {
        "id": 2,
        "projectName": "Cloud Migration"
    }
]'

Response

{
    "id": 1,
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "skills": ["Java", "Spring Boot"],
    "employmentHistories": [],
    "address": {
        "city": "New York",
        "state": "NY",
        "pinCode": 10001
    },
    "projects": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "projectName": "AI Development"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "projectName": "Cloud Migration"
        }
    ]
}


---

Steps to Follow

1. First, save projects using POST /projects


2. Then, assign projects to an employee using PUT /employees/{id}/assign-projects



Let me know if you need further clarifications!

